'''Dirty dog exercise''' or '''hip side lifts''' or ''fire hydrant exercise'' is an exercise that is meant to strengthen the [[hips]] and [[buttocks]], without the use of weights. It is so named due to resemblance to the way a dog urinates.<ref name="ultimatebodypress">{{cite web|url=http://www.ultimatebodypress.com/fire-hydrant.html|publisher=ultimatebodypress.com|title=Intermediate Pull Up Bar Dip Station Exercise - Fire Hydrant|accessdate=2017-04-06}}</ref><ref name="webmd">{{cite web|url=http://www.webmd.com/fitness-exercise/ss/slideshow-build-a-better-butt|publisher=webmd.com|title=Butt Exercise Pictures: Workouts for Slim and Shapely Glutes|accessdate=2017-04-06}}</ref> The exercise also improves [[core stability]].
