{{Infobox disease | Name = Parametritis | Image = | Caption = | DiseasesDB = | ICD10 = {{ICD10|N|73|0|n|70}}-{{ICD10|N|73|2|n|70}} | ICD9 = {{ICD9|614.4}} | ICDO = | OMIM = | MedlinePlus = | eMedicineSubj = | eMedicineTopic = | MeshID = D010249 | }} '''Parametritis''' is an [[inflammation]] of the [[parametrium]] ([[connective tissue]] adjacent to the [[uterus]]).
It is considered a form of [[pelvic inflammatory disease]].<ref name="urlBroad Ligament Disorders: eMedicine Obstetrics and Gynecology">{{cite web |url=http://emedicine.medscape.com/article/275773-overview |title=Broad Ligament Disorders: eMedicine Obstetrics and Gynecology |format= |work= |accessdate=2010-03-10}}</ref>
Parametritis is inflammation of the ligaments around the uterus. Parametritis is different from perimetritis which is inflammation of the serosa surrounding the uterus.
